  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Gender based violence in the Anglophone silent war</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">What began as a peaceful protest in Cameroon, in 2016, became a brutal and deadly situation for Southern Cameroonians resulting in the displacement of girls and women. Nigeria is hosting over 45,000 refugees from Southern Cameroon of which 80% are vulnerable women and children exposed to sexual violence. The turbulence of war and the desensitization of soldiers have endangered women and young girls, ages 10 years to 55 years, to sexual violence. This project intends to support 200 victims.</narrative>
  </description>
